Tweet Content:
Our reporter 
@NiallJournal_ie
 is on the Poland-Ukraine border, reporting on what refugees are experiencing as they flee the Russian invasion:

Ukraine foreign minister 
@DmytroKuleba
 said: “Putin has just launched a full-scale invasion of Ukraine. Peaceful Ukrainian cities are under strikes. This is a war of aggression. Ukraine will defend itself and will win. The world can and must stop Putin. The time to act is now."

Asked about reports that 
@Ryanair
 fares for those fleeing the #Ukraine conflict are 'shocking', Minister for Transport 
@EamonRyan
 says the Government will be in touch with the airline. He says Ryanair helped the Government get people out of difficult places during #Covid19

The United Nations Refugee Agency says about 3 million people have fled Ukraine since the Russian invasion, with most crossing into Poland. Our correspondent 
@emma_okelly
 and cameraman 
@PaulDeighano
 are in Zamość, about 60km from Ukraine, where the war is bringing back memories.

Taoiseach Micheál Martin said he is "deeply disturbed and saddened” by the killing of Irish citizen and journalist Pierre Zakrzewski in Ukraine. The Taoiseach heard the news while in Washington, where our correspondent 
@seanwhelanRTE
 has more on the news.

The United Nations says more than 2.8 million people have fled Ukraine since the Russian invasion began, with around 1.7 million having crossed into Poland. Our correspondent 
@emma_okelly
 and cameraman 
@PaulDeighano
 have spent today at the reception centre for refugees in Zamość.

Trucks that left Ireland last Tuesday as part of a large aid convoy bound for Ukraine have arrived in Eastern Poland. Our Correspondent 
@emma_okelly
 and cameraman 
@PaulDeighano
, are in Cieszanow in Eastern Poland.

'A desperate situation for refugees who don't know where they're going' | 
@RTENewsPaulC
 and 
@ocor1
 report from the from the Hrebenne checkpoint in Poland at the border with Ukraine

Sinn Féin Leader 
@MaryLouMcDonald
 says she will meet with the Ukrainian Ambassador and welcomes the support of the EU parliament condemning Russia's actions. Taoiseach 
@MichealMartinTD
 says the courage and resilience of the Ukrainian people is resonating across the globe.

Soc-Dem co-leader 
@CathMurphyTD
 says "Ireland is a neutral country but this does not mean we are neutral on the invasion of Ukraine". Taoiseach 
@MichealMartinTD
 says "unity of purpose is very important" in responding to Russia.

Sinn Féin leader 
@MaryLouMcDonald
 brings up the war in Ukraine. "Ireland more than most understands the impact of occupation and imperialist aggression." Taoiseach 
@MichealMartinTD
 says Putin is "a bully and a thug" and has unleashed an unjustifiable war on the people of Ukraine.

Caitriona Twomey of @PennyDinnersCor and a group of volunteers are travelling to Ukraine next week as part of a humanitarian convoy bringing essential supplies to the eastern European country. | 
